They must be super curious.

518
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:34,630
Right. It's driving them crazy.

519
00:16:35,430 --> 00:16:37,566
They said you should keep doing that because you looked cute.

520
00:16:37,590 --> 00:16:40,959
(I'm sorry that I scared you, Wannables.)

521
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:43,729
- Euratgotcha! - Euratgotcha!

522
00:16:43,730 --> 00:16:45,969
- It's meat! - It's meat!

523
00:16:45,970 --> 00:16:47,440
This looks so good.

524
00:16:47,770 --> 00:16:50,140
(Wanna One gets to enjoy a proper party.)

525
00:16:50,270 --> 00:16:53,540
- To Wanna One! - Cheers!

526
00:16:53,610 --> 00:16:54,779
(They take a short break.)

527
00:16:54,780 --> 00:16:56,420
(Sung Woon and Ji Hoon are taking a nap.)

528
00:16:57,010 --> 00:17:01,050
(Their day at the Wanna Base is full of joy.)

529
00:17:01,590 --> 00:17:03,990
Thank you. Euratgotcha!

530
00:17:04,590 --> 00:17:05,590
- What? - What?

531
00:17:05,860 --> 00:17:07,780
(It gets dark at the Wanna Base at that moment.)

532
00:17:08,690 --> 00:17:10,659
- My gosh. Hold on. - Hey.

533
00:17:10,660 --> 00:17:12,100
(Chaos)

534
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:13,160
- Hold on. - I'm sorry.

535
00:17:13,161 --> 00:17:14,799
I'm so scared.

536
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,399
- Get up. - I'm sorry.

537
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:18,340
- What's going on? - What is this?

538
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:20,039
Let's wake them up. Ji Hoon.

539
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:22,160
- The siren really scared me. - Members of Wanna One.

540
00:17:22,470 --> 00:17:23,570
(Yes? Us?)

541
00:17:23,810 --> 00:17:25,810
The car will leave in five minutes.

542
00:17:26,310 --> 00:17:28,150
(Running to get the members)

543
00:17:28,450 --> 00:17:30,049
Get all of your belongings...

544
00:17:30,050 --> 00:17:31,819
- and come out of the Wanna Base. - What?

545
00:17:31,820 --> 00:17:33,619
- I guess this place will blow up. - Hold on.

546
00:17:33,620 --> 00:17:36,100
- Hold on. What's going on? - I guess this place will blow up.

547
00:17:36,350 --> 00:17:37,350
- The car will leave in... - Oh, no!

548
00:17:37,351 --> 00:17:38,359
Five minutes.

549
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:39,360
- Hurry, Ji Hoon. - Hurry.

550
00:17:39,361 --> 00:17:40,519
- Wake up. - The car will leave...

551
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:41,730
in five minutes.

552
00:17:42,930 --> 00:17:44,530
They're caught off guard in their sleep.

553
00:17:46,860 --> 00:17:50,299
(Grabbing their belongings from their rooms)

554
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:52,140
The walnut cakes.

555
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:54,380
I have to grab the walnut cakes.

556
00:17:54,540 --> 00:17:56,509
- Wait. That's not important now. - The walnut cakes.

557
00:17:56,510 --> 00:17:58,410
I have to eat them on the way.

558
00:17:59,140 --> 00:18:01,239
Oh, right. My protein. I forgot to grab protein bars.

559
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:02,750
(Hoarding food just in case)

560
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:04,480
We have to get going now!

561
00:18:05,020 --> 00:18:06,779
Come on. Hurry up. The base is going to blow up.

562
00:18:06,780 --> 00:18:09,489
- We must slow down on the stairs! - That's not it.

563
00:18:09,490 --> 00:18:11,789
The base is about to blow up.

564
00:18:11,790 --> 00:18:13,020
Where is it?

565
00:18:13,790 --> 00:18:14,790
Where is it?

566
00:18:14,791 --> 00:18:17,689
- Please get in your personal car. - What?

567
00:18:17,690 --> 00:18:18,999
- Bye. - Bye.

568
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,499
I'm getting a feeling we might not see everyone there.

569
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:21,799
- Bye. - Okay.

570
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:23,199
- Wait, we won't see each other? - Let's meet again.

571
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:25,439
- We have to meet again. - Let's meet again.

572
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:26,600
Please.

573
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,110
Seriously. Don't forget me.

574
00:18:29,740 --> 00:18:31,680
- See you in a bit. - Can we?

575
00:18:31,810 --> 00:18:33,180
Where are we going?

576
00:18:34,110 --> 00:18:35,150
(See you soon.)

577
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:38,320
We usually take one car.

578
00:18:38,520 --> 00:18:40,219
But why are we suddenly taking our own car?

579
00:18:40,220 --> 00:18:41,590
Are we going to separate places?

580
00:18:42,550 --> 00:18:43,949
But I can't think of anywhere.

581
00:18:43,950 --> 00:18:45,190
What? Nine?

582
00:18:46,590 --> 00:18:47,590
Seven?

583
00:18:47,590 --> 00:18:48,590
Five?

584
00:18:49,260 --> 00:18:50,260
What's this?

585
00:18:50,261 --> 00:18:52,500
(They're assigned all different numbers.)

586
00:18:52,600 --> 00:18:53,860
Does it mean anything?

587
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:57,300
It's not like I ate six meals.

588
00:18:57,570 --> 00:18:59,739
Two? What could this number mean?

589
00:18:59,740 --> 00:19:00,740
(I'm 2nd?)

590
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:02,010
Two Dae Hwi?

591
00:19:02,340 --> 00:19:04,780
The number represents the order of arrival at the base today.

592
00:19:06,140 --> 00:19:07,840
I was the fifth one to arrive.

593
00:19:08,580 --> 00:19:11,949
(Their arrival number decided their fate.)

594
00:19:11,950 --> 00:19:14,350
(What will happen to them?)

595
00:19:14,690 --> 00:19:15,690
Okay.

596
00:19:17,320 --> 00:19:19,336
"Are you all right, Wanna One? I'm sure you're surprised by this."

597
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:21,119
"Starting now,"

598
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:22,660
"you are given a secret mission."

599
00:19:23,630 --> 00:19:25,360
"Your mission is..."

600
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:31,129
(Wanna One gets a secret mission, Don't Get Caught and Go.)

601
00:19:31,130 --> 00:19:33,469
"You must complete the mission before the shoot is over."

602
00:19:33,470 --> 00:19:35,439
"Once you complete the mission, you'll receive a huge benefit."

603
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:36,440
"So try your best."

604
00:19:36,810 --> 00:19:38,809
My gosh. A huge benefit? I'm curious now.

605
00:19:38,810 --> 00:19:40,770
So more than one person can complete the mission.

606
00:19:40,940 --> 00:19:42,579
Even if we get caught,

607
00:19:42,580 --> 00:19:44,356
we just have to complete it within the time limit?

608
00:19:44,380 --> 00:19:47,379
I guess everyone will have to do it secretly.

609
00:19:47,380 --> 00:19:48,789
It must be a secret mission.

610
00:19:48,790 --> 00:19:51,120
I see. Everyone will try to get in each other's way.

611
00:19:51,820 --> 00:19:53,290
I wonder if this could be a mission.

612
00:19:54,060 --> 00:19:56,860
Like getting someone to say something specific.

613
00:19:57,730 --> 00:19:59,159
"Your mission is..."

614
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:01,199
"singing Wanna One's song with a member in a relay."

615
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,906
I must do this with four different members?

616
00:20:02,930 --> 00:20:06,240
(He must sing the song in a relay with at least 4 members.)

617
00:20:06,540 --> 00:20:08,169
When I sing... Wing.

618
00:20:08,170 --> 00:20:09,170
Boomerang.

619
00:20:09,171 --> 00:20:11,270
(Going back and forth)

620
00:20:11,610 --> 00:20:14,479
"Collect one belonging from each member."

621
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:16,249
This sounds really fun. I love games like this.

622
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:18,720
"Make a balloon puppy that's the same as the photo."

623
00:20:20,220 --> 00:20:21,649
I really don't know how.

624
00:20:21,650 --> 00:20:23,289
Does anyone know how to make this?

625
00:20:23,290 --> 00:20:24,450
How do you make this?

626
00:20:25,290 --> 00:20:27,319
I'm really bad at craft.

627
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:30,729
"Have a conversation using 20 proverbs with the members."

628
00:20:30,730 --> 00:20:33,500
I can't use the same proverbs. My gosh. Okay.

629
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:35,299
"Hey, this is a piece of cake."

630
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:38,139
What if no one responds? That won't count?

631
00:20:38,140 --> 00:20:40,570
But they rarely respond to whatever I say anyway.

632
00:20:41,570 --> 00:20:43,410
I shouldn't have been the ninth one to arrive.

633
00:20:44,310 --> 00:20:45,709
Mine is the hardest, right?

634
00:20:45,710 --> 00:20:47,440
I can't do this in one day.

635
00:20:47,610 --> 00:20:50,950
I should've learned it in the military.

636
00:20:51,580 --> 00:20:54,579
(They set out to the mission spot with regrets and excitement.)

637
00:20:54,580 --> 00:20:56,340
I think I can be the first one to finish it.

638
00:20:56,490 --> 00:20:58,170
Will I get a benefit if I'm the first one?

639
00:20:58,460 --> 00:21:00,420
This looks pretty easy.

640
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:02,659
How did that song go? What is it?

641
00:21:02,660 --> 00:21:04,189
(Heart fluttering)

642
00:21:04,190 --> 00:21:05,906
They just have to sing the next part when I start it, right?

643
00:21:05,930 --> 00:21:07,399
I can borrow...

644
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,529
(Bae Bae is also strategizing.)

645
00:21:08,530 --> 00:21:11,740
lip balm from Dae Hwi or Ji Sung. That would work.

646
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:13,599
I'm a genius.

647
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:14,670
A genius.

648
00:21:15,770 --> 00:21:16,940
A circle.

649
00:21:17,540 --> 00:21:18,580
I have to twist it again.

650
00:21:19,410 --> 00:21:20,410
I don't know.

651
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:22,480
My gosh. I'm really not handy.

652
00:21:23,010 --> 00:21:26,650
(Lip trilling)

653
00:21:27,980 --> 00:21:29,289
I have a headache now.

654
00:21:29,290 --> 00:21:31,619
"Hey, let's do this together."

655
00:21:31,620 --> 00:21:33,890
"Two heads are better than one. You know?"

656
00:21:35,430 --> 00:21:37,136
I sounded like Writer Lim Seong Han, right?

657
00:21:37,160 --> 00:21:39,700
Once they figure it out, they won't do it with me.

658
00:21:39,900 --> 00:21:42,700
Some of the members catch on really fast.

659
00:21:43,070 --> 00:21:44,270
Especially Park Woo Jin.

660
00:21:44,570 --> 00:21:48,270
I don't even know where we're going. How can I plan anything?

661
00:21:49,470 --> 00:21:50,470
I don't know.

662
00:21:50,471 --> 00:21:52,380
I'll just roll with the punches this time.

663
00:21:52,540 --> 00:21:53,639
Where are we?

664
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:55,209
(They're getting close to the mission spot.)

665
00:21:55,210 --> 00:21:56,380
Why are we here?

666
00:21:57,550 --> 00:21:59,279
I see a strawberry field. Wait, is it not?

667
00:21:59,280 --> 00:22:00,579
(It's not.)

668
00:22:00,580 --> 00:22:01,950
Do you want us to dig the ground?

669
00:22:03,050 --> 00:22:04,290
It's raining, though.

670
00:22:05,720 --> 00:22:06,859
We're here.

671
00:22:06,860 --> 00:22:07,960
Where are we?

672
00:22:08,790 --> 00:22:09,790
Is this it?

673
00:22:09,791 --> 00:22:11,800
(Looking around)

674
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:13,559
- What's going on? - The van has to go.

675
00:22:13,560 --> 00:22:15,000
What do you think this place is for?

676
00:22:17,300 --> 00:22:18,660
That's the question I want to ask.

677
00:22:19,570 --> 00:22:20,670
What's this place?

678
00:22:21,070 --> 00:22:23,670
(Woo Jin can't contain his curiosity.)

679
00:22:25,680 --> 00:22:27,840
(Sticking out)

680
00:22:28,350 --> 00:22:30,650
(Wriggling)

681
00:22:32,220 --> 00:22:34,990
(He becomes a meerkat.)

682
00:22:35,490 --> 00:22:37,690
(But he doesn't have a single clue.)

683
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:40,059
All members, please come on out.

684
00:22:40,060 --> 00:22:41,159
Good luck.

685
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:42,320
(Good luck with the mission.)

686
00:22:43,390 --> 00:22:44,560
What is this place?

687
00:22:45,130 --> 00:22:46,229
(The members come out in a confused state.)

688
00:22:46,230 --> 00:22:47,230
What's this?

689
00:22:47,230 --> 00:22:48,230
(Meanwhile)

690
00:22:48,231 --> 00:22:49,800
Let me go over the proverbs once more.

691
00:22:51,130 --> 00:22:53,270
Keeping calm can save you from any situation.

692
00:22:53,640 --> 00:22:55,370
Fixing the stable after losing a cow.

693
00:22:55,940 --> 00:22:58,480
A poop-covered dog scolds a bran-covered dog.

694
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:00,640
Ruining the congee...

695
00:23:02,710 --> 00:23:04,949
- Hey, Ji Hoon. - Yes?

696
00:23:04,950 --> 00:23:06,279
- Ji Hoon. - Yes?

697
00:23:06,280 --> 00:23:07,280
What's yours?

698
00:23:08,290 --> 00:23:10,320
Ji Hoon, listen carefully.

699
00:23:10,550 --> 00:23:12,819
They say that keeping calm can save you from any situation.

700
00:23:12,820 --> 00:23:15,560
We can do this if we keep calm, okay?

701
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:20,199
You're the one who needs to keep calm.

702
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,830
You sound crazy.

703
00:23:22,630 --> 00:23:24,276
(Thanks to the unaware Ji Hoon, he uses 1 proverb!)

704
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:25,340
What's this place?

705
00:23:25,770 --> 00:23:27,199
What? There are clothes.

706
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:28,200
(Through the windows)

707
00:23:28,201 --> 00:23:29,310
There are clothes.

708
00:23:29,940 --> 00:23:31,339
Will we get our photos taken?

709
00:23:31,340 --> 00:23:32,379
Shall we go inside?

710
00:23:32,380 --> 00:23:34,220
- Shall we go inside? - One person is missing.

711
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:37,710
Seong Wu isn't here.

712
00:23:38,620 --> 00:23:39,649
Again?

713
00:23:39,650 --> 00:23:40,980
Why isn't he coming?

714
00:23:41,180 --> 00:23:43,289
Hey, let's just drop Seong Wu.

715
00:23:43,290 --> 00:23:44,419
Okay. Let's drop him.

716
00:23:44,420 --> 00:23:45,789
- Let's drop him. - Did he go home?

717
00:23:45,790 --> 00:23:46,959
Did he go home?

718
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:50,260
No. I saw him go somewhere while talking on the phone.

719
00:23:50,460 --> 00:23:51,659
- What? - Go where?

720
00:23:51,660 --> 00:23:53,759
As soon as he got out... We came this way, right?

721
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:55,070
Seong Wu went the other way.

722
00:23:56,670 --> 00:23:58,069
("Wanna Wants to Know")

723
00:23:58,070 --> 00:23:59,470
("Where did Mr. Ong disappear to?")

724
00:23:59,940 --> 00:24:02,040
(Before the vans left Wanna Base)

725
00:24:02,470 --> 00:24:04,070
"Your mission is..."

726
00:24:04,770 --> 00:24:08,140
"ordering and finishing jjajangmyeon by yourself."

727
00:24:09,210 --> 00:24:11,009
"Caution. You must have it delivered..."

728
00:24:11,010 --> 00:24:12,880
"and pick it up yourself."

729
00:24:13,080 --> 00:24:15,200
"You must finish the noodles for it to be a success."

730
00:24:15,390 --> 00:24:17,320
"You fail if anyone takes a bite."

731
00:24:17,890 --> 00:24:20,259
To be honest, I don't think this mission is too difficult.

732
00:24:20,260 --> 00:24:21,260
(Confident Ong)

733
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:25,100
(What are you doing?)

734
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:27,730
(Punching in)

735
00:24:28,470 --> 00:24:29,869
Okay. I have the address.

736
00:24:29,870 --> 00:24:30,969
(He figures out the address from the GPS.)

737
00:24:30,970 --> 00:24:32,570
(He is having fun already.)

738
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:34,840
Six minutes.

739
00:24:35,370 --> 00:24:37,010
(Proud Ong)

740
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:38,640
He is calling me.

741
00:24:39,210 --> 00:24:41,980
(He just needs to get the jjajangmyeon safely!)

742
00:24:43,550 --> 00:24:44,850
Seong Wu, where are you going?

743
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:47,849
(My best friend)

744
00:24:47,850 --> 00:24:48,850
It's nothing.

745
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:50,120
(Unsuspecting)

746
00:24:50,121 --> 00:24:51,620
(Does he need to use the restroom?)

747
00:24:52,920 --> 00:24:53,989
(He leaves Min Hyun and runs over to meet the deliveryman.)

748
00:24:53,990 --> 00:24:55,029
Hello.

749
00:24:55,030 --> 00:24:56,059
(He leaves Min Hyun and runs over to meet the deliveryman.)

750
00:24:56,060 --> 00:24:58,830
I'm at the front.

751
00:24:59,100 --> 00:25:00,700
(However)

752
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:02,700
What's this?

753
00:25:04,070 --> 00:25:06,700
(A giant truck blocks the narrow road.)

754
00:25:07,870 --> 00:25:09,869
(He can't get close until the truck leaves.)

755
00:25:09,870 --> 00:25:10,940
He is coming.

756
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:17,349
(Seong Wu's precious deliveryman)

757
00:25:17,350 --> 00:25:18,449
Watch out!

758
00:25:18,450 --> 00:25:20,850
(Sir, watch out for the truck.)

759
00:25:21,220 --> 00:25:23,790
(Backing off)

760
00:25:24,520 --> 00:25:27,320
(Nervous and anxious)

761
00:25:27,460 --> 00:25:29,630
(Even his back shows that he is in a hurry.)

762
00:25:29,830 --> 00:25:31,860
(A bit later)

763
00:25:33,930 --> 00:25:34,959
Oh, my.

764
00:25:34,960 --> 00:25:36,229
(Ong safely moves to the back of the truck.)

765
00:25:36,230 --> 00:25:37,270
Oh, my.

766
00:25:37,500 --> 00:25:40,140
(Finally, the truck leaves.)

767
00:25:40,470 --> 00:25:42,740
- Thank you. - Have a nice day.

768
00:25:43,440 --> 00:25:46,279
(Ong's perfect crime gets carried out successfully.)

769
00:25:46,280 --> 00:25:47,379
What are you doing?

770
00:25:47,380 --> 00:25:48,980
(Gosh, it's chirpy birdie!)

771
00:25:49,250 --> 00:25:50,509
(Chirpy birdie searched for the missing Seong Wu...)

772
00:25:50,510 --> 00:25:52,120
(and caught him.)

773
00:25:52,220 --> 00:25:53,519
- What are you doing? - What?

774
00:25:53,520 --> 00:25:55,040
- What's going on? - What do you mean?

775
00:25:55,920 --> 00:25:57,050
What?

776
00:25:57,620 --> 00:25:58,620
- Hey. - What is it?

777
00:25:58,621 --> 00:25:59,819
Carry out your mission.

778
00:25:59,820 --> 00:26:02,729
- What is it? - You have no reason to disturb me.

779
00:26:02,730 --> 00:26:04,429
Everyone is waiting because of you.

780
00:26:04,430 --> 00:26:05,699
- What? - Hurry up!

781
00:26:05,700 --> 00:26:07,730
- Don't be ridiculous. - Everyone is waiting.

782
00:26:08,260 --> 00:26:10,229
What's going on, Woo Jin?

783
00:26:10,230 --> 00:26:11,469
- What's going on, Woo Jin? - Is he carrying out a mission?

784
00:26:11,470 --> 00:26:13,299
- What? - What?

785
00:26:13,300 --> 00:26:14,540
It must be for his mission.

786
00:26:14,970 --> 00:26:16,839
- No. - Then what is it?

787
00:26:16,840 --> 00:26:18,616
- It isn't like that. - Let's take that away.

788
00:26:18,640 --> 00:26:21,110
(A suspicious-looking bag)

789
00:26:21,240 --> 00:26:22,249
- Let's take that away. - What?

790
00:26:22,250 --> 00:26:23,779
- What's this? - Grab it.

791
00:26:23,780 --> 00:26:25,079
- What's this? - Take it away.

792
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:26,249
- Give it to me. - What's this?

793
00:26:26,250 --> 00:26:27,519
I bet his mission is...

794
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:29,719
- bringing a food delivery. - It isn't like that.

795
00:26:29,720 --> 00:26:31,789
- It's eating jjajangmyeon. - That's right.

796
00:26:31,790 --> 00:26:33,019
It's eating jjajangmyeon.

797
00:26:33,020 --> 00:26:35,790
- Don't let him eat it. - Don't let him eat it.

798
00:26:35,830 --> 00:26:38,430
(Did he begin his mission already?)

799
00:26:39,230 --> 00:26:41,360
(Sung Woon runs.)

800
00:26:42,530 --> 00:26:44,329
What?

801
00:26:44,330 --> 00:26:46,069
- Let's go inside. - It begins when we go inside.

802
00:26:46,070 --> 00:26:48,299
- This is the start. - It begins when we go inside.

803
00:26:48,300 --> 00:26:49,369
Let's go.

804
00:26:49,370 --> 00:26:50,640
(However)

805
00:26:51,510 --> 00:26:52,979
- Hello. - What?

806
00:26:52,980 --> 00:26:53,980
Hello.

807
00:26:53,981 --> 00:26:55,150
- What? - What's this?

808
00:26:55,780 --> 00:26:56,979
- What? - It's a photo shoot.

809
00:26:56,980 --> 00:26:58,179
We'll have a photo shoot.

810
00:26:58,180 --> 00:27:00,020
A photo shoot? No way!

811
00:27:01,250 --> 00:27:05,120
(What's this place that calls for a cool shoot?)

812
00:27:06,190 --> 00:27:08,120
What... What are we doing?

813
00:27:08,530 --> 00:27:10,930
I thought we were carrying out our missions.

814
00:27:11,430 --> 00:27:13,799
- Hello. - Hello.

815
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:15,129
- Hello. - Hello.

816
00:27:15,130 --> 00:27:16,300
Is he an editor?

817
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:19,039
Hello, everyone.

818
00:27:19,040 --> 00:27:20,269
- Hello. - Hello.

819
00:27:20,270 --> 00:27:22,639
I'm Editor Park Chan.

820
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:24,970
Today, you'll have a photo shoot...

821
00:27:25,640 --> 00:27:26,909
for "Elle."

822
00:27:26,910 --> 00:27:28,309
(Excuse me?)

823
00:27:28,310 --> 00:27:29,550
(Startled)

824
00:27:29,680 --> 00:27:30,910
(Oh, my)

825
00:27:31,010 --> 00:27:32,419
- Are you serious? - It's a huge magazine.

826
00:27:32,420 --> 00:27:34,880
- Not "Wanna Magazine?" - No way.

827
00:27:35,450 --> 00:27:37,690
(Today is the day of Wanna One's photo shoot.)

828
00:27:38,290 --> 00:27:40,089
(It isn't for "Wanna Magazine.")

829
00:27:40,090 --> 00:27:43,590
(It's an actual photo shoot for a famous fashion magazine.)

830
00:27:45,130 --> 00:27:48,160
We're looking shabby at a very important place.

831
00:27:48,530 --> 00:27:50,799
For breakfast, we had tteokbokki,

832
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:52,900
hot bar, and popcorn.

833
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:55,309
We also ate ramyeon and meat.

834
00:27:55,310 --> 00:27:57,009
(They had a full meal a couple of hours ago.)

835
00:27:57,010 --> 00:27:58,010
(On top of that, )

836
00:27:58,011 --> 00:27:59,139
(they got covered in smoke during the barbecue party.)

837
00:27:59,140 --> 00:28:01,100
(They're looking shabby after getting rained on.)

838
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:03,479
We can't do this for "Elle."

839
00:28:03,480 --> 00:28:05,079
We're all worn out.

840
00:28:05,080 --> 00:28:07,219
We need a shower first.

841
00:28:07,220 --> 00:28:09,289
- Look at Sung Woon's hair. - It's no joke.

842
00:28:09,290 --> 00:28:10,319
Look at the back of his head.

843
00:28:10,320 --> 00:28:11,589
His hair is sticking out.

844
00:28:11,590 --> 00:28:13,060
What is he going to do?

845
00:28:13,420 --> 00:28:15,490
(Looking around)

846
00:28:16,060 --> 00:28:18,060
(Hold on! This is a good opportunity.)

847
00:28:18,260 --> 00:28:19,899
I knew that this would happen. This is why...

848
00:28:19,900 --> 00:28:21,329
This is why they say...

849
00:28:21,330 --> 00:28:22,546
(Lee Dae Hwi, you're my target!)

850
00:28:22,570 --> 00:28:24,599
- that everything must be checked. - I know.

851
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:25,899
We should've dug deeper.

852
00:28:25,900 --> 00:28:26,969
- I know. - Seriously.

853
00:28:26,970 --> 00:28:28,839
(Proverb sniper: Everything must be checked.)

854
00:28:28,840 --> 00:28:30,110
(He shot it perfectly.)

855
00:28:30,270 --> 00:28:32,510
Will you be okay with such models?

856
00:28:32,740 --> 00:28:34,039
(Of course.)

857
00:28:34,040 --> 00:28:37,109
After each member gets their hair and makeup done,

858
00:28:37,110 --> 00:28:39,349
they'll put on an outfit that matches the concept...

859
00:28:39,350 --> 00:28:41,050
and proceed with the solo shots.

860
00:28:41,080 --> 00:28:42,220
(Oh, my!)

861
00:28:42,590 --> 00:28:44,189
(They're fully prepared!)

862
00:28:44,190 --> 00:28:45,190
Really?

863
00:28:45,191 --> 00:28:48,259
In that case, do we need to do the mission before the end...

864
00:28:48,260 --> 00:28:49,589
of the photo shoot?

865
00:28:49,590 --> 00:28:51,389
Carry out your mission...

866
00:28:51,390 --> 00:28:53,730
before the end of the photo shoot.

867
00:28:54,460 --> 00:28:55,669
- Well, - It'll be so much fun.

868
00:28:55,670 --> 00:28:57,469
This is a piece of cake for all of us.

869
00:28:57,470 --> 00:28:58,769
We're used to this.

870
00:28:58,770 --> 00:29:00,540
I don't want to eat this piece of cake.

871
00:29:00,900 --> 00:29:01,900
Would you like hot food instead?

872
00:29:01,901 --> 00:29:03,539
I want hot food now.

873
00:29:03,540 --> 00:29:04,869
- Okay. Let's eat something hot. - But...

874
00:29:04,870 --> 00:29:06,386
(He has already used 3 proverbs in a conversation.)

875
00:29:06,410 --> 00:29:09,479
Now, you'll get ready and proceed with the photo shoot.

876
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:12,750
- How are we supposed to get ready? - Seriously.

877
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:15,749
We'll need to massage our underarms.

878
00:29:15,750 --> 00:29:17,350
To reduce bloating?

879
00:29:17,950 --> 00:29:19,690
We need to massage our earlobes.

880
00:29:20,290 --> 00:29:22,160
This is so sudden.

881
00:29:22,590 --> 00:29:24,290
I'm in trouble.

882
00:29:25,630 --> 00:29:26,630
(The trouble...)

883
00:29:26,631 --> 00:29:27,859
(Hurried)

884
00:29:27,860 --> 00:29:29,429
(The trouble hasn't even begun.)

885
00:29:29,430 --> 00:29:30,430
(A murderous look)

886
00:29:30,870 --> 00:29:32,069
(Wanna One's chaotic photo shoot)

887
00:29:32,070 --> 00:29:33,099
(Worked up)

888
00:29:33,100 --> 00:29:34,500
(Crying)

889
00:29:36,010 --> 00:29:37,980
(You can see the next episode right away!)
